Saleginella was known as a key ingredient in the resurrection ritual performed by Taoist priests. It was known as the resurrection plant due to its unique property of curling and shriveling up into a bud-like shape when dried and uncurling, spreading healthy green leaves when accumulating enough moisture. So what if these plants can actually resurrect cadavers? What if they can take control of cadavers like a parasite taking control of its host? It would be a sight to see corpses being reanimated

The Goal for this was to design a vehicle that operates on both land and water. So immediately I thought about amphibious animals and their forms. So the first two picks were an alligator and a duck. The last one was a pivot spitball idea of land, water, and air. Although a stingray isn’t an amphibious animal, its form makes for great aerodynamic design and purposes, so I gave that a try in my priliminary exploration and sketching phase. I ended up going with the duck form for its less aggresive and balanced form.
